            <h1 class="mt-4">MATCHUP MATH PRIVACY POLICY</h1>
            <!-- Post Content -->
            <p class="lead">Effective Date: 28  September 2021</p>
            <p class="lead">This Privacy Policy governs your use of the software application Matchup Math (also referred to as <b>“MaTcHup”</b>, <b>“App”</b>, <b>“Application”</b>, <b>MaTcHup App”</b>, or <b>“Services”</b>) for mobile devices and the website <a href="{{\URL::to('')}}">https://yizegames.com</a> (“Website” or the <b>“Site”</b>); both of which are owned and operated by Olive’s Kid Inc.. We refer to the App and Site collectively as the "Services. We respect and take your privacy seriously and are committed to protecting it through our compliance with this policy. The Application is a math game for both Android and iOS phones. </p>
            <p class="lead"><b>Data Controller:</b> Data Controller means the natural or legal person who (either alone or jointly or in common with other persons) determines the purposes for which and the manner in which any personal information are, or are to be, processed. For the purpose of this Privacy Policy, we are a Data Controller of your Personal Data. We can be reached via email at: <a href="mailto:oliveskidinc@gmail.com">oliveskidinc@gmail.com</a></p>
            
            <p class="lead">This Privacy Policy (the <b>“Policy”</b>) describes the types of information we may collect from you or that you may provide when you use the Services. It also covers our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting and disclosing that information. This Policy applies to data collected: (i) by Matchup through the Site or App, and (ii) in email, text or other electronic messages between you and us as a result of using App. This Privacy Policy does not apply to information collected offline, by any third party or through our affiliate sites. We reserve the right to modify or amend the terms of our privacy policy from time to time without notice. Please note, your continued use of the Services constitutes your agreement to this Policy.  And your continued use of our Services following the posting of changes to these terms will mean you accept those changes.</p>

            <p class="lead">Also, as the use of technology rapidly evolves, so too is Matchup’s use of new and evolving technology. We strongly encourage you to revisit this Policy from time to time for any updates regarding our use of this technology and how it relates to your information.</p>

            <p class="lead"><b>Information We Collect</b></p>
            <p class="lead">When you use our Services, we receive data from which we collect certain information about how you use and interact with our Services, including;</p>
            <ol>
              <p class="lead">
                <li>
                  <b>User Account:</b>When registering a Matchup user account we collect the following Personal Data: (1) your name, (2) email address, (3) year of birth (only for the purpose of setting the level of difficulty in the game). Your user account is protected by a password that is provided by you.   
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Device information:</b> We collect information about your device such as your hard drive model, operating system version, unique device identifier, mobile data usage and IP address.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Daily Log:</b> When you use our Services or access information we provide, we will automatically collect certain information, saving it to the daily logs on our servers. This type of information collection is usually triggered by events like crashes, system activities, changes in hardware settings and login requests. 
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Unique App Serial Number:</b> Certain Services include unique app serial numbers. When you install or uninstall one of these Services or when the Service communicates with us like in the event of a software update, the system will send us the serial number and installation information such as your operating system type and the app version number.   
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>IP ADDRESS:</b> When you download and use our Services, we do not collect your Internet Protocol ("IP") address. However, please note that we use Admob which is a mobile advertising network that helps app developers monetize and promote their mobile and tablet apps with ads.  Admob is owned by Google. Admob may collect your (“IP”) address so we encourage anyone who uses are services to read the Google/Admob privacy policy here: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>COOKIES AND WEB BEACONS:</b> A “cookie” is a piece of text that is placed on your computer's hard drive. A persistent cookie remains on your hard drive after you close your browser and may be used by your browser on subsequent visits to a Service. Persistent cookies can be removed by following your web browser’s directions. A session cookie is temporary and disappears after you close your browser. You can reset your web browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. We use traffic log cookies to identify which pages are being used. This helps us analyze data about web page traffic and tailor App to customer needs. A cookie in no way gives us access to your computer or any information about you, other than the data you choose to share with us. However, you can choose to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can modify your browser settings to decline cookies if you prefer. Note, this may prevent you from taking full advantage of the App and their features.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>ANALYTICS COOKIES:</b> We use web analytic app to understand how people use our App, as well as keep our App relevant, easy to use and up-to-date. Cookies allow web analytic app to recognize your browser or device, but do not contain Personal Information.  
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>LOCATION INFORMATION:</b> This Application does not collect precise information about the location of your mobile device.
                </li>
              </p>
            </ol>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Consent as a Basis for Processing</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">In some cases, we will ask for your consent to access your Contacts. Contact details will be uploaded and stored on the server for the purpose of sending SMS invites and challenge request notifications when the server has verified which contacts either have downloaded the app or those who have not yet installed the app. You may indicate your consent in a number of ways, including, as permitted by law, clicking ‘Okay’ button (or equivalent action) to indicate your consent when (i) providing us with your Personal Data through our Services (ii) registering or creating an account with us. We may request your consent for a number of activities including:</p>
            <ol>
              <p class="lead">
                <li>
                  <b style="margin-bottom: 5px;display: block;">Accessing Contacts to Invite Users</b>
                  <p class="lead">We may request your consent to access your Contacts. This allows you to seamlessly invite people to download the app. Contact details will be uploaded and stored on the server for the purpose of sending an SMS invite and then to verify the contact when the invite is accepted. </p>   
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b style="margin-bottom: 5px;display: block;">Challenge Them in Multiplayer</b>
                  <p class="lead">We also may request your consent to access your Contacts so that those individuals who have also downloaded the Matchup Math app can be sent a challenge request notification when you wish to play a game in multiplayer mode.</p>   
                </li>
              </p>
            </ol>
            <p class="lead"><b>OUR POLICY REGARDING CHILDREN</b></p> 
            <p class="lead">
              Generally speaking, our mobile application and website are not intended for children under the age of 13 (and those under the age of 16 years old who reside in the UK or European Countries) (collectively, “Children”). Children are not permitted to use our Services, and we do not knowingly collect, store or use any personal information from Children. 
            </p>
            <p class="lead">Though our Services do not target Children as the primary user, we do collect age information during the sign up process to establish a baseline for the starting level of difficulty for the Matchup Math game. In the event that a user identifies himself or herself as a child under the age of 13 during the sign up process via our age-gate, we will terminate the effort to create an account.</p>
            <p class="lead">If we learn that we have inadvertently gathered personal information from a Child, we will take reasonable measures to promptly remove that information from our records.</p>
            <p class="lead">If you believe we might have any information from a child, please contact us at <a href="mailto:oliveskidinc@gmail.com">oliveskidinc@gmail.com</a></p>
            <p class="lead"><b>Your Opt-Out Rights</b></p>
            <p class="lead">
                <u>Opt-out of all information collection by uninstalling the Application:</u> You can stop all collection of information by the Application easily by uninstalling the Application. You may use the standard uninstall processes as may be available as part of your mobile device or via the mobile application marketplace or network.
            </p>
            <p class="lead"><b>Deleting Your Account</b></p>
            <p class="lead">
              If you wish to delete your Matchup Math account, please contact us at <a href="mailto:oliveskidinc@gmail.com">oliveskidinc@gmail.com</a>  - We will make reasonable efforts to delete your account in a timely manner.  
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Use of Information </b>
            </p>          
            <p class="lead">We may use collected information as follows:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><p class="lead">Any information collected by our Services may be used to maintain, protect and improve those Services, as well as to develop new Services and protect our users. We may also use this information to provide you tailored content such as ads with a high degree of relevancy.</p></li>
              <li><p class="lead">When you contact us, we may save your correspondence record, which can help to solve problems you may encounter. We may send you Service related emails such as notifications about upcoming changes or improvements.</p></li>
              <li><p class="lead">We may use information collected by other technologies to improve your user experience and the overall quality of our Services.</p></li>
              <li><p class="lead">To serve advertisements in our Services using third-party advertising networks, our legal basis is legitimate interests to run our business.</p></li>
            </ul>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Application Hosting</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">Matchup Math uses Amazon AWS to host its mobile application. AWS provides on-demand access to scalable web and application servers, storage, databases, content delivery, cache, search, and other application services.</p>
            <p class="lead">Amazon AWS: <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/privacy/" target="_blank">https://aws.amazon.com/privacy/</a></p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Links to Other Sites</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">Our Services may direct you to third party websites when you click on banner ads or other types of advertiser links. Our provision of a link to a third party website is not in itself an endorsement of that third party or its security policies. We exercise no control over websites that belong to our advertising partners or third parties, which may place their own cookies on your device or solicit personal information from you. When you leave our Services to visit an external website, you submit to the external website’s privacy policy, which we encourage you to read fully. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of third party websites and their use of information will be in accordance with their own privacy policies. <b><u>Your use of a third party website is at your own risk</u></b> and we cannot be held liable from any damages, costs, fees or penalties arising or resulting from your use of third party sites.</p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Third-Party Use of Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">Some content or applications, including advertisements, through the App are serviced by a third-party, including advertisers, ad networks and servers, content providers and application providers. These third parties may use cookies alone or in conjunction with web beacons or other tracking technologies to collect information about you when you use our App. The information they collect may be associated with your Personal Information or they may collect information, including Personal Information, about your online activities over time and across different app. They may use this information to provide you with interest-based (behavioral) advertising or other targeted content. We don’t control these third parties' tracking technologies or how they may be used. If you have any questions about an advertisement or other targeted content, you should contact the responsible provider directly.</p>
            <p class="lead">Data collected by these third party services (even if offered on or through Matchup Math) is not received by us. As such, the use of our service is subject to these third party Privacy Policies:</p> 
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p class="lead">Admob (<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>)</p>
              </li>
