            <p class="lead">
              <b>Sharing Your Personal Information</b>
            </p>

            <p class="lead">We do not sell, trade, or rent Personal Information to third parties for direct marketing. However, we may share generic aggregated demographic information (such as the total number of visitors) not linked to Personal Information with our business partners and trusted affiliates.</p>
            <p class="lead"><b>We may also:</b></p>

            <p class="lead">Disclose information: (i) To fulfill the purpose for which you provide it (for example, to initiate communication with other users or facilitate a pickup); (ii) For any purpose disclosed by us when you provide the information; (iii) To comply with any court order, law or legal process, including a response to any government or regulatory request; (iv) To investigate, prevent, or take action regarding suspected or actual illegal activities or take precautions against liability; (v) If we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of us or others (vi) With affiliates or subsidiaries; or (vii) With the public where information is posted to a public forum.</p>

            <p class="lead">Any Personal Information you voluntarily disclose for posting to the Service, becomes available to the public as controlled by any applicable privacy settings. If you remove information that you posted to the Service, copies may remain viewable in cached and archived pages of the Service, or if other users have copied or saved that information. Matchup may also retain information after you delete your account if required by law; such information is needed for investigation purposes or for archival purposes.</p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>How We Secure Personal Information</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to secure Personal Information. When you provide Personal Information we do our best to ensure it’s encrypted via SSL. However, none of these are fail-proof, and we ask for your cooperation in ensuring your information stays safe. Please note we may discard any information: (i) after your account has been cancelled or terminated, (ii) upon your request; or (iii) any time in our sole discretion, whichever occurs earlier.</p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Data Retention Policy, Managing Your Information</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
              We will retain User provided data for as long as you use the Application and for a reasonable time thereafter. We will retain Automatically Collected information for up to 24 months and thereafter may store it in aggregate. If you’d like us to delete User Provided Data that you have provided via the Application, please contact us at <a href="mailto:oliveskidinc@gmail.com">oliveskidinc@gmail.com</a> and we will respond in a reasonable time. Please note that some or all of the User Provided Data may be required in order for the Application to function properly.
             </p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Complaint or Inquiry</b>
            </p>  
            <p class="lead">
            If you have any questions, concerns, or comments about our Privacy Policy or practices, please contact us via email at <a href="mailto:oliveskidinc@gmail.com">oliveskidinc@gmail.com</a> with the words "PRIVACY POLICY" in the subject line.
            </p>

            <p class="lead">
              <b>Internet Security and Possible Risks</b>
            </p>
               
            <p class="lead">Matchup cannot warrant the security of data while in transit to or from our App. By using a Service, you will be deemed to have assumed such risks.</p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Geographic Restrictions, Applicable Law </b>
            </p>  
            <p class="lead">The App may only be accessed within the USA and Canada. Any claim relating to the App shall be governed by the internal laws of the State of California without reference to its choice of law provisions, and shall be resolved solely through proceedings held within the State of California.</p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Notification of Privacy Policy Changes</b>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">Matchup has the discretion to update this Privacy Policy at any time. When we do, we will revise the updated date at the bottom of this page. We encourage users to frequently check this page for any changes to stay informed about how we are helping to protect the Personal Information we collect. If we make material changes, we will notify you through a notice.</p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Privacy Rights for California, North Dakota and Vermont Residents</b>
            </p>   
            <p class="lead"><b>California.</b> A California resident may request us not to share Personal Information with a third party. Existing California users can provide us with their order ID, name, and email address and postal address either by email at <a href="mailto:oliveskidinc@gmail.com">oliveskidinc@gmail.com.</a> <b>In case of any email inquiry, users will receive a computer generated reply confirming our receipt.</b> In accordance with California Civil Code Sec. 1789.3, California resident users are entitled to know that they may file grievances and complaints with California Department of Consumer Affairs, 1625 North Market Blvd., Suite N 112 or by phone at <a href="tel:800-952-5210">800-952-5210.</a></p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>North Dakota.</b> Pursuant to state law, we will only share information with our service providers and with third parties as required or permitted by law or as permitted by you.
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
              <b>Vermont.</b> We will not disclose information about you with our affiliated companies or with Non-Affiliated Third Parties, other than as required or permitted by law or permitted by you.
            </p>
